                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12634758" author="stack" created="Fri, 26 Sep 2008 06:01:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For now, here is a workaround:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
hbase(main):019:0&amp;gt; disable &apos;TestTable&apos;
# HBaseAdmin has already been imported into the shell during startup and &apos;@configuration&apos; is the shells HBaseConfiguration instance.
hbase(main):010:0&amp;gt; admin = HBaseAdmin.&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt;(@configuration)
# In my instance, only one table so can &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; index &apos;0&apos; of returned list
hbase(main):011:0&amp;gt; htd = admin.listTables()[0]
hbase(main):017:0&amp;gt; htd.setMaxFileSize(67108864)  
hbase(main):018:0&amp;gt; admin.modifyTableMeta(Bytes.toBytes(&apos;TestTable&apos;), htd)
hbase(main):019:0&amp;gt; enable &apos;TestTable&apos;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12635174" author="stack" created="Sat, 27 Sep 2008 18:18:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When a fix, confirm can set cache flush size too from shell &amp;#8211; MEMCACHE_FLUSHSIZE &amp;#8211; and that can set table READONLY.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12640878" author="apurtell" created="Sun, 19 Oct 2008 21:14:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-902&quot; title=&quot;Add force compaction and force split operations to UI and Admin&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-902&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-902&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; changes how the workaround Stack describes is done within the shell in lieu of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-800&quot; title=&quot;support HTD and HCD get/set attribute in shell, Thrift, and REST interfaces&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-800&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-800&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12667021" author="viper799" created="Sat, 24 Jan 2009 23:47:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updates to add to roadmap for 0.20.0. &lt;br/&gt;
We should at lease support this in shell for users that do not use java to have access to these features&lt;br/&gt;
Thrift and rest support can come down the road in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-800&quot; title=&quot;support HTD and HCD get/set attribute in shell, Thrift, and REST interfaces&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-800&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-800&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12668054" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 28 Jan 2009 15:35:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch that changes &quot;alter&quot; so it accepts something like :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
alter &apos;t1&apos;, {METHOD =&amp;gt; &apos;table&apos;, MAX_FILESIZE =&amp;gt; &apos;10485760&apos;, MEMCACHE_FLUSHSIZE =&amp;gt; &apos;1048576&apos;, READONLY =&amp;gt; &apos;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&apos;}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12668217" author="stack" created="Wed, 28 Jan 2009 23:16:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1  I tested it and it works.  Nice fix for shell functonality.  Only think I&apos;d change, though I would not put this in the way of the commit, is the method name.  &apos;table&apos; is super generic.  &apos;table_attributes&apos; seems a bit long.  I&apos;ll live if &apos;table&apos; goes in but maybe you have a better name j-d?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12668516" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 29 Jan 2009 16:53:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review and trying my patch, I changed &quot;table&quot; to &quot;table_att&quot;. I committed this to trunk but I think it fixes something important so I would put it in 0.19 branch unless someone has an objection.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12669252" author="jdcryans" created="Sat, 31 Jan 2009 21:27:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to 0.19 branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
